    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Estimate gas basically does what it says, it **estimates** the gas usage of a transaction. It always depends on the current state of the network. If the data in the contract changes, the gas usage might also change. For example if you modify a storage slot that wasn't modified before it costs more than changing a storage slot that was accessed previously. Additionally setting a storage slot to zero gives you a refund. Thus there are a lot of things that can change between estimating gas an sending the actual transaction. \r\n\r\nDoes that answer your question? In the future please use the ethereum stackoverflow https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/",
